rComments: Took both macro and micro with him, he makes his expectations very particular, he also breaks down the complex material into relatively simple concepts. Good prof in general.

One of the most interesting profs who goes much beyond just the book. He makes the course easy to do with his package. The exams are hard but he explains well by relating economics to everyday life.

Intimidating and always seems to be angry. He makes a lot of jokes but for me, they didn't make the class any better. Moves very fast although might be because I took the course in the summer. He's an okay prof, didn't really know what he was talking about at times; but he does want us to learn and pass the course. The TAs were very helpful so tutorials are definitely good to go to.

He is a very grumpy prof, i wonder if he smiles lol HOWEVER, he is excellent. He does a good job at explaining concepts and relating them to everyday life. As long as you do his practice questions and go to class you will do well.
awesome.
Prof.Keiran encourages all to  relate the course material with current economy situation and economic decisions. He's always up for questions and makes effort to clear the doubts.
Difficult, but worth it. Very entertaining, and will not hesitate to help you outside of class hours. Devoted to the learning of his students.

Furlong is an amazing prof. The material is difficult but he definitely provides enough opportunities to practice. His sample exams are helpful, and if you put the work in, your marks will reflect that. Seminars are invaluable for clarification. Overall, great prof, hard material, but you get out whatever effort you put in.

Furlong is an amazing prof. Seriously he keeps the classes attention, and makes all the material simple to understand. He will make 3 hours fly by!
great prof, that expects his students to know whats going on in everyday life, very helpful!
